cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.SI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a novel optical data center network architecture and presents an algorithm for DCN topology reconfiguration. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper focuses on data center network architecture. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) is a possible category as the paper discusses a new technology (RODCA) that augments an existing architecture (PODCA). 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a possible category as the paper discusses the design and implementation of a new data center network architecture. 
- cs.SI (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the optimization of network topology to dynamic traffic.
